org.opentosca.toscana.model.capability

Class EndpointCapability

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentosca.toscana.model.BaseToscaElement
      • org.opentosca.toscana.model.capability.Capability
        • org.opentosca.toscana.model.capability.EndpointCapability
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VisitableCapability
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AdminEndpointCapability, DatabaseEndpointCapability, PublicEndpointCapability

    public class EndpointCapability
extends Capability
    This is the default type that should be used or extended to define a network endpoint capability. This includes the information to express a basic endpoint with a single port or a complex endpoint with multiple supportedPorts. By default the Endpoint is assumed to represent an address on a private network unless otherwise specified. (TOSCA Simple Profile in YAML Version 1.1, p. 153)
